REC Sees Depreciation Charges at $180 Million in Second Half

-- B y   M a r i a n n e   S t i g s e t
-- 
2011-07-19T05:18:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/rec-sees-depreciation-charges-at-180-million-in-second-half.html
Renewable Energy Corp. ASA, a
Norwegian maker of solar energy components, said that after the
impairment charges in the second quarter, depreciation and
amortization in the second half of 2011 is estimated to
approximately 1 billion kroner ($180 million).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marianne Stigset at 
 mstigset@bloomberg.net  